{% block title %}Placeholder Classes{% endblock %}
{% block content %} 
<section class="content">

  <h2>Placeholder Classes</h2>
<p>
  The purpose of placeholder classes in Brass Tacks is to help reduce the number of classes
  that have duplicate code.  Extend these placeholders into Project Specific classes you create
  to leverage the pre-built code base.
</p>
<p>
  As placeholders aren't included in CSS unless they're exteneded into a class, you can also
  remove any extensions you don't currently need from Brass Tacks, without having to delete the
  code entirely, incase you ever do have a use for a placeholder.
</p>

<hr />

<h3>Brand</h3>
